### MCP Server - Demo HTTP Requests
### Use with the VS Code REST Client extension

### =====================================================
### Local Development Endpoints
### =====================================================

@localBaseUrl = http://localhost:7071

### Health Check (Local)
# Shows which agents are registered and their configurations
GET {{localBaseUrl}}/api/health

###

### Joker Agent (HTTP only)
# This agent is configured with HTTP trigger only (default)
POST {{localBaseUrl}}/api/agents/Joker/run
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Tell me a joke about programming.",
  "thread_id": "joker-thread-001"
}

###

### PlantAdvisor Agent (HTTP + MCP)
# This agent is configured with both HTTP and MCP tool triggers
POST {{localBaseUrl}}/api/agents/PlantAdvisor/run
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "What plant would you recommend for a low-light office?",
  "thread_id": "plant-thread-001"
}

###

### StockAdvisor Agent - HTTP endpoint disabled
# Note: This request will fail because StockAdvisor only has MCP trigger enabled
# It can only be invoked via the MCP protocol, not HTTP
POST {{localBaseUrl}}/api/agents/StockAdvisor/run
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "What's the current price of MSFT?",
  "thread_id": "stock-thread-001"
}

###

### =====================================================
### Azure Deployed Endpoints
### Replace <your-function-app-name> with your actual Function App name
### =====================================================

@azureBaseUrl = https://<your-function-app-name>.azurewebsites.net

### Health Check (Azure)
GET {{azureBaseUrl}}/api/health

###

### Joker Agent (Azure)
POST {{azureBaseUrl}}/api/agents/Joker/run
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Tell me a joke about the cloud.",
  "thread_id": "azure-joker-001"
}

###

### PlantAdvisor Agent (Azure)
POST {{azureBaseUrl}}/api/agents/PlantAdvisor/run
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "What plants are good for air purification?",
  "thread_id": "azure-plant-001"
}
